&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Band 7 Job Advert&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employer:&lt;/strong&gt; Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Department:&lt;/strong&gt; Finance Department&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Leeds &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary:&lt;/strong&gt; £38,890 to £44,503&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Job Title: Research and Innovation Accountant&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Level: Band 7 - £38,890 to £44,503&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;37.5 hrs/week, Permanent contract&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;It is an exciting time to join Leeds Teaching Hospitals NHS Trust and be part of our award winning finance team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you would like to play your part and gain exposure to all the fantastic opportunities that being part of the team presents; then there is the chance for you to join us as one of our Research and Innovation Accountants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust has an enviable track record of working with leading industrial and academic partners to deliver internationally acclaimed research and innovation; our research income is around £21m and growing. The finance team is playing its part in driving forward and supporting this agenda, working in close partnership with clinicians and other colleagues.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Whilst the role has an R&amp;I focus, it is integrated within one of our financial management teams and the successful candidate will be exposed to other areas of work, responsibility and training and development. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We want to hear from enthusiastic individuals, who have two years R&amp;I experience and who are committed to continuous improvement and can deliver financial advice and information which is accurate, timely and value added.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; A genuine desire to help us continue on our journey as a finance team to “to be the best” and to successfully engage and communicate with our many stakeholders will be key attributes we are looking for.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you are attracted by what you have just read and feel you can offer what we are looking for, then we are really keen to hear from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you want to know more, then please contact Simon Revesai Senior R&amp;I Accountant at simon.revesai@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
